'''''Star Wars'' 20''' is the twentieth issue in the ''[[Star Wars: Republic]]'' series of comics. It was published on [[July 26]], [[2000]] by [[Dark Horse Comics]].

==Publisher's summary==
''Quinlan Vos searches for his past&mdash;and the Devaronian Villie is his reluctant helper. First stop, the home of Bib Fortuna, right-hand man to the nefarious Jabba the Hutt! Can Quin resist the pull of the dark side when dealing with lowlifes like Bib? His search for the mysterious woman, Aayla, will take him from a band of thugs to a stolen ship pursued by smugglers! Get on board and see if he makes it!''

==Plot summary==
As Quin sleeps, he dreams of his lost [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]], Aayla Secura. He explains to his Devaronian companion, that before leaving [[Nar Shaddaa/Legends|Nar Shaddaa]], the must find [[Bib Fortuna/Legends|Bib Fortuna]], who also showed up in his visions. After finding him and squeezing as much information from him as possible, he is able to summon his guards. Quin and Villie are able to repel the attackers, but in the meantime, Fortuna is able to escape. After a narrow escape from the planet's surface, Quinlan decides the best place to begin the search for his identity is his home planet of [[Kiffu/Legends|Kiffu]]. Once there, Quinlan learns of his recent investigation from his great-aunt [[Sheyf]] [[Tinté Vos]]. Meanwhile, back aboard the [[Inferno (Vilmarh Grahrk)|''Inferno'']], Villie finds out about a bounty on Quin's head from his cousin [[Holmar Grahrk|Holmar]].

